.TH OPEN_XDATACHANNEL 8 "2025" "xmm7360-pci" "System Administration"
.
.SH NAME
open_xdatachannel \- initialise and configure the Intel XMM7360 LTE modem
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B open_xdatachannel
.RB [ \-a
.IR apn ]
.RB [ \-i ]
.RB [ \-D
.IR device ]
.RB [ \-n ]
.RB [ \-m
.IR metric ]
.RB [ \-t
.IR seconds ]
.RB [ \-r ]
.RB [ \-c
.IR file ]
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B open_xdatachannel
initialises the Intel XMM7360 / Fibocom L850 LTE modem over its PCIe RPC
channel, attaches to the mobile network, opens the data channel, and
configures the
.B wwan0
network interface with the assigned IP address and default route.
.PP
It replaces the original Python-based
.I open_xdatachannel.py
with no runtime dependencies beyond standard system libraries.
.PP
When used with the
.B xmm7360
kernel module (recommended), run with
.B \-\-init\-only
to wake the modem and let ModemManager and NetworkManager handle the
rest.  Full data-channel mode is intended for use with the
.B iosm
kernel module.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-a " apn" ", \-\-apn " apn
Mobile network APN (e.g.\&
.IR internet ).
Required unless
.B \-\-init\-only
is used.
.TP
.B \-i ", \-\-init\-only"
Initialise the modem (SIM, FCC unlock, RF on, signal reporting) then
exit without opening the data channel.  Use this with the
.B xmm7360
kernel module so that ModemManager can detect the SIM and manage
connectivity via NetworkManager.
.TP
.BI \-D " path" ", \-\-device " path
Path to the RPC character device.
Auto-detected if not specified; tries
.I /dev/xmm0/rpc
then
.IR /dev/wwan0xmmrpc0 .
.TP
.B \-n ", \-\-nodefaultroute"
Do not install the modem as the default route for IP traffic.
.TP
.BI \-m " metric" ", \-\-metric " metric
Metric (priority) for the default route.  Higher values mean lower
priority.  Default:
.BR 1000 .
.TP
.BI \-t " seconds" ", \-\-ip\-fetch\-timeout " seconds
Retry interval in seconds when polling for an IP address from the modem.
Default:
.BR 1 .
.TP
.B \-r ", \-\-noresolv"
Do not append modem-provided DNS servers to
.IR /etc/resolv.conf .
.TP
.BI \-c " file" ", \-\-conf " file
Read configuration from
.I file
in addition to the default locations.
.
.SH INITIALISATION SEQUENCE
Regardless of mode,
.B open_xdatachannel
always performs the following steps over the RPC channel:
.PP
.RS
UtaMsCbsInit, UtaMsNetOpen, UtaMsCallCsInit, UtaMsCallPsInitialize,
UtaMsSsInit, UtaMsSimOpenReq, FCC unlock, UtaModeSet(online),
UtaMsNetSetRadioSignalReporting, UtaMsNetSetRadioSignalReportingConfiguration,
UtaMsNetSingleShotRadioSignalReportingReq
.RE
.PP
In full mode (without
.BR \-\-init\-only )
it then continues with network attach, data channel setup, IP
configuration, and interface bring-up.
.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Failure — error message written to standard error.
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /dev/xmm0/rpc
RPC character device created by the
.B xmm7360
kernel module.
.TP
.I /dev/wwan0xmmrpc0
RPC character device created by the
.B iosm
kernel module.
.TP
.I /etc/resolv.conf
DNS nameservers provided by the modem are appended here unless
.B \-\-noresolv
is given.
.
.SH EXAMPLES
Wake the modem for ModemManager (typical use with xmm7360 module):
.PP
.RS
.B open_xdatachannel \-\-init\-only
.RE
.PP
Full data-channel setup with iosm module:
.PP
.RS
.B open_xdatachannel \-\-apn internet
.RE
.PP
Full setup with explicit device path and no default route:
.PP
.RS
.B open_xdatachannel \-a internet \-D /dev/wwan0xmmrpc0 \-n
.RE
.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mmcli (1),
.BR nmcli (1),
.BR ModemManager (8),
.BR NetworkManager (8),
.BR ip (8),
.BR dkms (8)
.
.SH AUTHORS
Originally developed as part of the
.B xmm7360\-pci
project.
C port and packaging by contributors.
.
.SH BUGS
Power management is not supported.  The modem loses its configuration on
system suspend and must be reinitialised on resume.  Run
.B open_xdatachannel \-\-init\-only
after resume or configure a systemd sleep hook to do so automatically.
